content: Not sure if this is the right place to put this: I've been using Reach to survey friends and family. The two issues that come up 90% of the time are stopping Trump and reproductive rights, but neither is in the list of issues. Is there a reason for that? Will it change any time soon? (hope this doesn't sound unpleasant, I think you are all doing an amazing job!!) Thanks.

There should be information on reproductive rights in the library. 
https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1269401955755888720/1283188705745702912/Single_Issues_in_Reach_App.png?ex=66e2161b&is=66e0c49b&hm=2567c0c1e6579b82de54c2f63b4901226279000363cb5099de7bbd0028926e69&
I wasn't clear. In Reach there are tags for issues the person cares about, but no tags for reproductive rights or preserving democracy which are the two I get most often. Thanks!
